description: David Earl Smith I rarely post political rants on FB, but I need to make an exception. Liberal friends, I have a favor to ask you. Conservatives, I want to talk to you too, but liberal friends first.  Liberals, I see your posts and know you don't like Trump's ultra-conservative behavior. I frequently don't like it either, but I don't mind it at all compared to what's actually bothering me. The thing that's actually bothering me gets mentioned from time to time, but is almost never directly addressed in posts I've seen. Everyone thinks being a conservative is the greater evil. And, just as I think I'm the only one who sees the real problem, John Oliver to the rescue.   https://m.youtube.com/watch?v=xecEV4dSAXE  I think the wall is likely a bad idea. But it's hardly the first time we've spent 20 billion dollars on a bad idea. It probably wouldn't even represent a large fraction of the amount we're spending yearly on bad ideas. And we can fix relations with Mexico after Trump. Let the Republicans have their bad ideas.  The problem is the LYING. That's the only actual problem. All other things are tolerable in comparison. The alternative facts. The fake news. The North Korea/1984-esque doublethink. (Watch the linked video please.)  Liberals, here is my favor. Please stop trying to falsely equivocate being conservative with believing you don't need to worry about the facts. One of those should wholly strike you as a larger problem than the other. Even if you believe they're correlated, one is still the larger problem. A conservative who respects the facts should be, for all of us, preferable to any candidate whatsoever who does not.  Democrats, the Republicans kicked your ass in November. (Fact.) It's their turn. If you want something, you have to go through them. (Fact.) I want something. Please help me get it. Republicans may be your enemy, but on this issue, any Republican who believes lying is wrong is on your side. Recruit that person to stand with me. Show them respect. Agree to disagree on anything less important. Even if they disagree about this most critical issue, don't unfriend them. Don't block them. Don't disrespect them. Don't harden their heart to this issue. We need to play for the long game with those people, because everyone should believe that facts are facts. Come to think of it, even once we resolve this issue, keep that strategy for the next issue. It's just better than the strategy you've been using.  Conservatives, if you already see this problem, great. Let's fix this issue and then Republican the shit out of this country together. Obamacare? Gone. Want a wall? Let's build two! (Canada's going to be a problem too once we're done with how great we're going to make this place again.) It's your turn, fair and square. And that's important.  I have a favor to ask you conservatives too. Don't feel like you need to stand by Trump in order to be a good conservative. They truly are different things, and happen to be even more different now than usual. (Family values much?) Help me keep him accountable to the truth, or help me remove him and send a message to every future president that misinformation and doublethink will not be tolerated.  Liberals, no more equivocating.   # penceforpresident Richard Lester Travis Hudson Michael Brooks Nancy McCollough Kelsey Cvach
